00:07.920 --> 00:15.040
with me a very good friend of mine and one of our ableist and most progressive and hard-hitting

00:15.040 --> 00:16.040
senators.

00:16.040 --> 00:22.920
A senator from Texas, Mr. Ralph, Senator Ralph Yarbrough, and thank you very much Ralph for

00:22.920 --> 00:24.720
coming and being with us today.

00:24.720 --> 00:25.720
Thank you, Senator.

00:25.720 --> 00:28.480
Keep all for this opportunity to be on your program.

00:28.480 --> 00:33.120
We've watched your record for years and the House of Representatives where TVA was being

00:33.120 --> 00:37.480
set up since you've been in the Senate, your crime investigations, your investigation

00:37.480 --> 00:42.640
of monopoly, the high price of steel, the high price of drugs, all of the many services

00:42.640 --> 00:44.400
you've rendered to American people.

00:44.400 --> 00:46.560
I know Ralph and I just want everybody to understand.

00:46.560 --> 00:47.960
I didn't put you up to this.

00:47.960 --> 00:49.960
I know the ground rules.

00:49.960 --> 00:54.040
You're not supposed to brag on the man when you own his program, but as this I'm breaking

00:54.040 --> 00:57.760
the rules because I think this is important and I just want to say it.

00:57.760 --> 01:04.280
I made a number of speeches for you in Texas in 1956 when you were running for Vice President

01:04.280 --> 01:06.600
on the Democratic Ticket and I'm proud of everyone.

01:06.600 --> 01:10.280
Well, you're certainly a dad and I appreciated you helping us too.

01:10.280 --> 01:14.000
Ralph, incidentally, a lot of your people come from Tennessee, don't they?

01:14.000 --> 01:15.000
Oh, yes.

01:15.000 --> 01:16.400
My grandfather was born in Tennessee.

01:16.400 --> 01:21.040
My paternal grandfather, Yarbrough, and from the old age pension records, social security

01:21.040 --> 01:26.280
and others, all the records we have, we know that more people have come to Texas from Tennessee

01:26.280 --> 01:27.960
than from any other state in the Union.

01:27.960 --> 01:28.960
That's right.

01:28.960 --> 01:29.960
That's right.

01:29.960 --> 01:33.580
Left there by Sam Houston, David Crockett, and many other Tennessee heroes who led the

01:33.580 --> 01:36.300
westward march of the American people into Texas.

01:36.300 --> 01:42.320
Well, there's always been a very close relationship between the State of Texas and the State of Tennessee.

01:42.320 --> 01:48.360
But friends, I've asked Senator Yarbrough here today to talk with him about federal,

01:48.360 --> 01:51.080
talk with you about federal aid for education.

